    <section class="support-content">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div id="intro" class="col-12">
                    <h1>Support when you need it</h1>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
        <section class="support-content">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <p>Nervous about starting your course at Newcastle University London? There's no need to be! On arrival, you will get involved in a range of activities to help you prepare for your academic journey. As well as supporting you academically and professionally, we're here to give you the personal support you need to thrive at university. From campus tours to registering for classes, or even how to open a bank account, we'll help you prepare for life as student in London.</p>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <hr />
        </section>
            <section class="support-content">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Getting settled in London</h2>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <p>Freshers’ induction week</p>
<p>Your first term starts with a social programme called ‘Freshers’ week’ –
there are no lectures, just lots of fun events to help you connect with
other students. These activities typically include:</p>
<ul>
<li>boat trip on the River Thames</li>
<li>food, pizza, tea and cake receptions</li>
<li>'meet and greet’ with academics</li>
<li>The Freshers’ Fair – see what you can get involved in whilst you’re studying</li>
<li>tours and local area activities to help you make the most of our fantastic location</li>
<li>evening socials in local restaurants, bars and clubs</li>
<li>activities specifically for international students to help you settle into life in a new country and city.</li>
</ul>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <hr />
        </section>
            <section class="support-content">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-12">
                        


